! CPL Server Plugin

This plugin provides the server-side API used by the TiddlyWiki CPL (Community Plugin Library).

!! Features

* Download statistics with IP-based throttling
* Rating submission with one-vote-per-IP enforcement
* Changelog lookup for plugin tiddlers
* Comment submission and moderation APIs
* GitHub OAuth based authentication for moderation flows

!! API Endpoints

* POST /cpl/api/download/:pluginTitle
* GET /cpl/api/download-plugin/:pluginTitle
* GET /cpl/api/stats
* GET /cpl/api/stats/:pluginTitle
* POST /cpl/api/rate/:pluginTitle
* GET /cpl/api/changelog/:pluginTitle
* GET /cpl/api/comments/:pluginTitle
* POST /cpl/api/comments/:pluginTitle
* GET /cpl/api/comments/pending
* PUT /cpl/api/comments/:pluginTitle/:commentId
* GET /cpl/api/auth/status
* GET /cpl/api/auth/github/callback?code=...

!! Storage

Server data is stored under the data/ directory:

* data/stats*.json for download counters
* data/ratings*.json for rating data
* data/comments/*.json for comment records

!! Notes

* The server supports read-only TiddlyWiki mode.
* Multi-server deployments can use CPL_SERVER_ID to separate writable files.
* Back up the data/ directory regularly.
